Uncle Henrik came back from fishing one day and said “I have a surprise.” while saying that Ellen with outstretched arms ran to Annemarie and hugged her and said “It’s so good to see you again!” While Ellen hugged Annemarie, Annemarie gave the Star of David to Ellen and said “I believe this is yours.”  “Thanks.” Ellen replied A few seconds later Mr and Mrs Rosen came in and Mr and Mrs Johansen gave them beers and a handshake.  ”This calls for a celebration.” said Kirsti.  “Do you three girls  want to go play outside while we talk?” said Papa. “Ok” the girls replied. Then went out the door. Annemarie, Ellen, Kirsti and Thor all played together by picking flowers, playing tag.  Soon they got tired and sat down next to the ocean.  “ Hey do you remember when we ran down Osterbrogade” said Annemarie  “Yeah, that was terrifying.” Ellen replied “Same.” “I wasn't. Kristy sayed proudly  “It felt like yesterday tho.” said Annemarie ignoring Kirsti.  Two hours later Mama called the girl in. When they got in the lights were out. Then turned on. Then Mr and Mrs Johansens shouted “surprise!”,  A banner saying “Welcome Back!” was hung up and little steamers were on the ceiling dangling down. On the table was a cute little chocolate cake with the words “Welcome Back Rosens!” frosted on the top of the cake.  Just then, Mr. and Mrs. Rosen came in from the other room and looked at the room in awe. ”This is too much.” said Mrs. Rosen. ”It’s the least we can do.” replied Mama. “It is just that, we missed you so much.”  Soon they sat down and  started eating the cake discussing what the Rosens missed in Copenhagen.  “I lost my to front teeth” said Kirsti proudly showing her teeth. “Good for you Kirsti!” replied Ellen “I hope the tooth fairy come to get your teeth.” “She did.” Kirsti said holding up
